Gianluigi Donnarumma has indirectly confirmed that Gonzalo Higuain will be leaving AC Milan to join Chelsea, saying: &ldquo;Gonzalo will have had his reasons if he&rsquo;s decided to leave and I wish him all the best of luck because he&rsquo;s a great friend and I have a lot of respect for him.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Meanwhile, Milan have already moved to replace Higuain, with Krzystof Piatek set to join. Genoa coach Cesare Prandelli told Sky Sport Italia: &ldquo;When I arrived here, there was no intention to sell him, but then the club decided to evaluate this option. There&rsquo;s no need beating ourselves up about it, we&rsquo;ve just got to make the most of the players we do have available.&rdquo;
